SIMPLE: crankle
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Crankle
<hw>Cran"kle</hw> <pr>(kr?n"k'l)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Cf.
<er>Crinkle</er>.]</ety> <def>To break into bends, turns, or angles; to
crinkle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Old Veg's stream . . . drew her humid train aslope,⟦br⟧
<qex>Crankling</qex> her banks.</q> <rj><qau>J. Philips.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Crankle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Crankle
<hw>Cran"kle</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To bend, turn, or
wind.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Along the <qex>crankling</qex> path.</q>
<rj><qau>Drayton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Crankle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Crankle
<hw>Cran"kle</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A bend or turn; a twist; a
crinkle.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Crankness</ent>⟦br⟧
